  "texts": [
    "The derivative should also be minimized, as both the residual and its deriva-tive should be zero at the correct solution.",
    "However, a general problem in the cost function formulation persists.",
    "The cost function should correspond to the norm of the error, which is not necessarily the case.",
    "This means that a reduction in the cost does not necessarily yield an improvement in quality of solution.",
    "The error norm can be expressed in terms of the H -1 -norm, which, according to [288], can efficiently be computed on rectangular domains with Fourier transforms."
  ],
